<paragraph blockId="9.[130,775,1300,1517]" box="[132,232,1300,1326]" pageId="9" pageNumber="292">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[130,775,1300,1517]" pageId="9" pageNumber="292">
Our specimens are very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Cordell, 1952" authorityName="? Cordell" authorityYear="1952" box="[492,775,1331,1358]" class="Ostracoda" family="Bairdiidae" genus="Acratia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="9" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recurvata">
<emphasis box="[492,620,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="292">A. recurvata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="CORDELL R. J." box="[625,775,1331,1358]" pageId="9" pageNumber="292" pagination="74 - 112" refId="ref18495" refString="CORDELL R. J. 1952. - Ostracodes from the Upper Pennsylvanian of Missouri. Part I. The Bairdiidae. Journal of Paleontology 26: 74 - 112." type="journal article" year="1952">Cordell, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Late Pennsylvanian (Late Carboniferous) of 
<collectingRegion box="[681,774,1363,1389]" country="United States of America" name="Missouri" pageId="9" pageNumber="292">Missouri</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[138,193,1395,1421]" name="United States of America" pageId="9" pageNumber="292">USA</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="CORDELL R. J." box="[201,341,1395,1422]" pageId="9" pageNumber="292" pagination="74 - 112" refId="ref18495" refString="CORDELL R. J. 1952. - Ostracodes from the Upper Pennsylvanian of Missouri. Part I. The Bairdiidae. Journal of Paleontology 26: 74 - 112." type="journal article" year="1952">Cordell 1952</bibRefCitation>
) and Late Permian of South 
<collectingCountry box="[633,699,1395,1421]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="292">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="SHI C. G. &amp; CHEN D. Q." pageId="9" pageNumber="292" pagination="47 - 129" refId="ref20505" refString="SHI C. G. &amp; CHEN D. Q. 2002. - Late Permian Ostracodes from Heshan and Yishan of Guangxi. Bulletin of Nanjing Institute Geology and Paleontology, Academic Sinica 15: 47 - 129 (in Chinese with English abstract)." type="journal article" year="2002">Shi &amp; Chen 2002</bibRefCitation>
) but differ in having a more concave AVB, a VB slightly concave at mid-L and the PDB connection with DB forming a more or less marked angle.
</paragraph>
